<p>
 Note that in the limit $\hbar \to 0$, the integral in the definition of $K(x_0, x_1)$ is dominated by the contribution from the neighborhood of critical points of the action. For finite-dimensional integrals of this form, method of stationary phase allows one to write asymptotic expansion in powers of $\hbar $. 
</p>
